quorum-->
We take odd number of master nodes in kubeadm because etcd consensus needs majority quorum. Odd numbers maximize fault-tolerance while minimizing wasted capacity.
Q. how ur pod will ping external domain like google.com or on-prem domain or database?

eksctl upgrade cluster --name my-eks-1-32-cluster --region us-east-1 --approve

eksctl delete cluster --name my-eks-1-32-cluster --region us-east-1

eksctl update addon --cluster my-eks-1-32-cluster --region us-east-1 --name kube-proxy --force

eksctl update addon --cluster my-eks-1-32-cluster --region us-east-1 --name coredns --force

eksctl update addon --cluster my-eks-1-32-cluster --region us-east-1 --name vpc-cni --force


aws eks update-nodegroup-version --cluster-name my-eks-1-32-cluster --region us-east-1 --nodegroup-name my-nodes --kubernetes-version 1.33

aws eks list-nodegroups --cluster-name my-eks-1-32-cluster

aws eks list-addons --cluster-name my-eks-1-32-cluster
